OL,3,CCraig Bellamy accepts cheering against
OL,4,CEngland was wrong
OL,6,F"I trusted the disciplinary process
OL,7,Fand respected it," Bellamy said when
OL,8,Fasked how he had come through that
OL,9,Fdifficult period.
OL,11,F"I understood, as well, there's a lot
OL,12,Fof stuff I didn't know ` like cheering
OL,13,Fagainst England in a game in front of
OL,14,Fpeople from England. It's not correct.
OL,15,FYou can't do that.
OL,17,F"I didn't know that. I honestly
OL,18,Fthought it was just nature for me. I
OL,19,Fdidn't understand how a young 18-year-
OL,20,Fold English boy might have felt.
